Structures

Footer

The footer is loaded on every page.

Note: As footers are usually unique to the project, the actual components and styling being used are coded into the Structure rather than being pulled from a data file.
Still, the use of yml data is encouraged once the design is finalized.

Navigation

The sitewide navigation, composed of the Navbar Component (ext) and Button Basic.
Mobile view adds a hamburger menu. The Order and Seach buttons disappear on smaller screens as their journeys are not mobile safe.

Options as passed by the data:

  • id the id used for the hamburger menu functionality. Defaults to site-menu
  • classes a list of classnames for the navbar container
  • is-fixed setting this to 1 stickies the navigation bar to the top of the page. This also adds a .has-navbar-fixed-top to the html. Default is 0
  • is-centered setting this to 1 places all menu items in the center of the available width. Default is 0
  • items a list of menu items
    • text the text of the item
    • subitems a list of submenu items
      • text the text of the submenu item
      • is-active setting this to 1 adds a visual indicator to the item. Default is 0
      • is-divider setting this to 1 omits the text and adds a horizontal divider instead
